translated: Eriksson, Josef Teodor, high school teacher, Motala, b. 22/12/90 in Vena, Kalmar 1., son of sawmill owner Johan E. and Charlotta Nilsdotter. — Graduated from high school in Linköping in 1914, Bachelor of Arts in 1917, Master of Theology in 1922, passed practical theology exam, ordination exam and ordination in 1926, probation year at Södra Latin in Stockholm 1924-25. Traveled to Germany and Czechoslovakia in 1929, Finland in 1933, and Germany and Switzerland in 1938. Acting subject teacher at the municipal intermediate school from 1922-24, Acting Lecturer at Karlstad People's Seminary from 1925-26, teacher in Östersund from 1926-28, teacher at AUS in Uppsala from 1928-29, teacher in Eskilstuna from 1929-30, substitute lecturer and substitute teacher in Nyköping from 1930-32, teacher of religion and mother tongue at Motala high school since 1937. Author of "A Family Chronicle from Sevede and Tunalän" (1946) and articles in the Hobby magazine, interested in family research. Married in 19XX.
